The APAC Group Personal Insurance Pricing and Portfolio Management team was created to support the actuarial pricing, portfolio management and business intelligence duties for Group Personal Insurance products across APAC geographies.
The pricing team within the Group Personal Insurance organization provides actuarial rate reviews and other analytical support associated with product reviews, product development, new business opportunities, profitability analysis, and client reviews. This group also leverages internal and external data, along with classical actuarial techniques and predictive modeling to support its mission.
We are looking for an Actuarial Analyst who will assist in executing the aforementioned tasks across the Greater China, Australasia, and Southeast Asia geographies. This role will also have a key responsibility in supporting the maintenance of the rating tools for group insurance products to ensure consistency across the APAC geographies.
Primary Responsibilities:
Maintaining the rating tools for group insurance products in the APAC geographies. This requires regular communication and engagement with various stakeholders around the region to ensure that the rating tools meet their business requirements;
Provide training to local underwriters in the region on best practices in utilizing the rating tools;
Assist in pricing and rate reviews of Personal Accident, Travel and Warranty Service products on both individual account and overall portfolio basis using key actuarial techniques;
Provide support for experience study on a regular basis to recommend pricing guidelines;
Assist in portfolio reviews of major accounts and segments, identifying key issues and opportunities from a growth and profitability perspective;
Assist in annual budgeting process where required;
Support rate filings where required
Position Requirements
Fluency in English and Mandarin, both written and spoken, including being able to read and write complex insurance terms in Mandarin;
Bachelor’s Degree, preferably in Mathematics, Statistics, or Actuarial Science;
At least 2-3 years of actuarial experience in a life and/or non-life insurance industry. Understanding of the basic actuarial concepts and product knowledge in Asian markets is crucial;
Proficiency in MS Excel, Access, Power Point, SAS and/or any predictive modeling tool;
Good interpersonal and cross-cultural skills with strong communication skills;
Strong analytical and problem solving skills with good attention to details;
Excellent time management skills and the ability to manage conflicting priorities
